### 2.4 Database Schema (Supabase)

#### Table: `cim_creative_assets`
Stores each ad creative as an asset with metadata.

```sql
CREATE TABLE cim_creative_assets (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  brand TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (brand IN ('fgs','ff','ip','fp','ss')),
  platform TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (platform IN ('meta','google','tiktok','pinterest','snapchat')),
  ad_account_id TEXT NOT NULL,
  campaign_id TEXT,
  ad_set_id TEXT,
  ad_id TEXT NOT NULL,
  creative_type TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (creative_type IN ('image','video','carousel','collection','playable')),
  creative_url TEXT,              -- URL to the creative asset (image/video/thumbnail)
  creative_hash TEXT,             -- Deduplication hash
  thumbnail_url TEXT,             -- Thumbnail for videos
  status TEXT DEFAULT 'pending',  -- pending | tagging | tagged | error
  tagging_started_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
  tagging_completed_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),
  updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
);

CREATE INDEX idx_cim_assets_brand ON cim_creative_assets(brand);
CREATE INDEX idx_cim_assets_platform ON cim_creative_assets(platform);
CREATE INDEX idx_cim_assets_status ON cim_creative_assets(status);
CREATE INDEX idx_cim_assets_ad_id ON cim_creative_assets(ad_id);
```

#### Table: `cim_creative_tags`
Stores individual element tags extracted from each creative.

```sql
CREATE TABLE cim_creative_tags (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  asset_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES cim_creative_assets(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  tag_category TEXT NOT NULL,     -- See Tag Taxonomy below
  tag_name TEXT NOT NULL,         -- The specific tag value
  tag_value TEXT,                 -- Optional qualifier (e.g., confidence score, timestamp in video)
  confidence FLOAT DEFAULT 1.0,  -- AI confidence (0.0-1.0)
  source TEXT DEFAULT 'gpt4o',   -- Which AI model extracted this
  frame_timestamp FLOAT,         -- For video: seconds into clip where element appears
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
);

CREATE INDEX idx_cim_tags_asset ON cim_creative_tags(asset_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_cim_tags_category ON cim_creative_tags(tag_category);
CREATE INDEX idx_cim_tags_name ON cim_creative_tags(tag_name);
CREATE INDEX idx_cim_tags_category_name ON cim_creative_tags(tag_category, tag_name);
```

#### Table: `cim_tag_performance`
Aggregated performance metrics per tag, recalculated daily.

```sql
CREATE TABLE cim_tag_performance (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  tag_category TEXT NOT NULL,
  tag_name TEXT NOT NULL,
  brand TEXT NOT NULL,
  platform TEXT NOT NULL,
  date_range_start DATE NOT NULL,
  date_range_end DATE NOT NULL,
  -- Aggregated metrics across all creatives with this tag
  creative_count INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
  total_spend NUMERIC(12,2) DEFAULT 0,
  total_impressions BIGINT DEFAULT 0,
  total_clicks BIGINT DEFAULT 0,
  total_conversions INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
  total_revenue NUMERIC(12,2) DEFAULT 0,
  -- Calculated KPIs
  avg_ctr NUMERIC(8,6) DEFAULT 0,
  avg_cpc NUMERIC(8,4) DEFAULT 0,
  avg_cpa NUMERIC(10,2) DEFAULT 0,
  avg_roas NUMERIC(8,4) DEFAULT 0,
  avg_conversion_rate NUMERIC(8,6) DEFAULT 0,
  -- Statistical confidence
  sample_size INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
  statistical_significance BOOLEAN DEFAULT false,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),
  updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),
  UNIQUE(tag_category, tag_name, brand, platform, date_range_start, date_range_end)
);

CREATE INDEX idx_cim_perf_tag ON cim_tag_performance(tag_category, tag_name);
CREATE INDEX idx_cim_perf_brand ON cim_tag_performance(brand);
CREATE INDEX idx_cim_perf_roas ON cim_tag_performance(avg_roas DESC);
```

#### Table: `cim_fatigue_alerts`
Predictive fatigue detection results.

```sql
CREATE TABLE cim_fatigue_alerts (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  asset_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES cim_creative_assets(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  alert_type TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (alert_type IN ('early_warning','declining','critical','fatigued')),
  severity INTEGER CHECK (severity BETWEEN 1 AND 5),
  metrics_snapshot JSONB NOT NULL,   -- { ctr_7d_ago, ctr_now, roas_7d_ago, roas_now, frequency, ... }
  decline_rate NUMERIC(8,4),         -- % decline per day
  estimated_days_remaining INTEGER,  -- Predicted days until creative dies
  recommendation TEXT,               -- AI-generated recommendation
  acknowledged BOOLEAN DEFAULT false,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
);

CREATE INDEX idx_cim_fatigue_asset ON cim_fatigue_alerts(asset_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_cim_fatigue_type ON cim_fatigue_alerts(alert_type);
CREATE INDEX idx_cim_fatigue_severity ON cim_fatigue_alerts(severity DESC);
```

### 2.5 Tag Taxonomy (42 Tag Categories)

The AI tagger must extract elements across these categories:

#### Visual Elements (Image + Video)
| Tag Category | Example Tags | Description |
|-------------|-------------|-------------|
| `hook_type` | question, bold_claim, statistic, pain_point, curiosity_gap, before_after, social_proof | Opening hook style |
| `hook_text` | (actual text extracted) | Exact hook text/dialogue |
| `cta_type` | shop_now, learn_more, get_started, claim_offer, limited_time, swipe_up | Call-to-action style |
| `cta_text` | (actual text extracted) | Exact CTA text |
| `visual_style` | ugc, lifestyle, studio, flat_lay, product_closeup, split_screen, testimonial, meme, infographic | Creative visual format |
| `color_palette` | warm, cool, neutral, high_contrast, pastel, dark, bright | Dominant color scheme |
| `primary_color` | (hex code) | Primary brand/accent color used |
| `text_overlay` | yes, no | Whether text is overlaid on image |
| `text_amount` | minimal, moderate, heavy | Amount of on-screen text |
| `face_present` | yes, no | Whether a human face is visible |
| `face_count` | 0, 1, 2, 3+ | Number of faces visible |
| `face_emotion` | happy, serious, surprised, excited, concerned, neutral | Dominant facial expression |
| `face_gender` | male, female, mixed, ambiguous | Perceived gender of face(s) |
| `face_age_range` | 18-24, 25-34, 35-44, 45-54, 55-64, 65+ | Estimated age range |
| `product_visible` | yes, no | Whether the product is shown |
| `product_prominence` | hero, secondary, background, absent | How prominently product features |
| `lifestyle_context` | home, outdoor, office, gym, kitchen, travel, social | Setting/environment |
| `logo_present` | yes, no | Brand logo visibility |
| `social_proof_type` | testimonial, review_score, user_count, before_after, celebrity, award | Type of social proof element |
| `urgency_element` | countdown, limited_stock, limited_time, none | Urgency/scarcity element |
| `offer_type` | discount_percent, discount_dollar, bogo, free_shipping, bundle, free_trial, none | Offer presentation |

#### Video-Specific Elements
| Tag Category | Example Tags | Description |
|-------------|-------------|-------------|
| `video_duration` | 0-6s, 6-15s, 15-30s, 30-60s, 60s+ | Duration bucket |
| `hook_timing` | 0-1s, 1-3s, 3-5s | When the hook lands |
| `scene_count` | 1, 2-3, 4-6, 7+ | Number of distinct scenes |
| `pacing` | fast, medium, slow | Cut speed/energy level |
| `music_type` | upbeat, calm, dramatic, trending, none | Background music style |
| `voiceover` | yes_male, yes_female, yes_ai, no | Voiceover presence and type |
| `caption_style` | kinetic_text, subtitle, none | How captions/text appear |
| `transition_style` | cut, fade, swipe, zoom, none | Dominant transition type |
| `aspect_ratio` | 1:1, 4:5, 9:16, 16:9 | Creative aspect ratio |

#### Copy/Text Elements
| Tag Category | Example Tags | Description |
|-------------|-------------|-------------|
| `headline_formula` | how_to, number_list, question, command, testimonial, news | Headline copywriting formula |
| `primary_text_length` | short_1-2_lines, medium_3-5_lines, long_6+_lines | Primary text length |
| `tone` | professional, casual, urgent, empathetic, humorous, authoritative | Copy tone of voice |
| `pain_point` | (extracted pain point text) | Pain point referenced |
| `benefit` | (extracted benefit text) | Core benefit highlighted |
| `mechanism` | (extracted mechanism text) | Unique mechanism/how it works |
| `price_shown` | yes, no | Whether price is explicitly shown |
| `guarantee` | money_back, satisfaction, results, none | Guarantee type mentioned |

#### Strategic Elements
| Tag Category | Example Tags | Description |
|-------------|-------------|-------------|
| `funnel_stage` | awareness, consideration, conversion, retention | Target funnel position |
| `audience_signal` | broad, interest, lookalike, retarget, custom | Inferred audience target |
| `customer_avatar_match` | (avatar ID from registry) | Which customer avatar this targets |
| `competitive_angle` | direct_comparison, category_claim, unique_mechanism, price_war | Competitive positioning |

### 2.6 AI Tagging Pipeline (SOP)

#### Step 1: Asset Ingestion
- Pull new/updated ad creatives from UMDM tables (`umdm_ads`) every 6 hours
- For each new creative, download or capture the creative asset (image URL or video URL from the ad platform API)
- Insert into `cim_creative_assets` with status = `pending`

#### Step 2: AI Element Extraction
For each `pending` creative asset:

**For Images:**
1. Send image to OpenAI GPT-4o Vision API
2. Use this system prompt:

```
You are a performance marketing creative analyst. Analyze this ad creative image and extract ALL elements using the tag taxonomy provided. For each element, return a JSON array of tags.

TAG TAXONOMY:
[Include the full tag taxonomy table above]

Rules:
- Extract EVERY applicable tag. Be thorough.
- For text elements (hook_text, cta_text, pain_point, benefit, mechanism), extract the EXACT text visible.
- For subjective tags (emotion, tone, style), provide your best assessment.
- Confidence: 1.0 for clearly visible elements, 0.7-0.9 for inferred elements, <0.7 for uncertain.
- Return ONLY valid JSON. No markdown, no explanation.

Output format:
{
  "tags": [
    {"category": "hook_type", "name": "question", "value": null, "confidence": 0.95},
    {"category": "hook_text", "name": "Are you tired of...", "value": null, "confidence": 1.0},
    ...
  ]
}
```

**For Videos:**
1. Extract keyframes at: 0s, 1s, 3s, every 5s thereafter, and last frame
2. Send each keyframe to GPT-4o Vision with the same prompt (add `frame_timestamp` context)
3. If audio track exists: transcribe using Whisper API, then analyze transcript for:
   - `hook_text` (first 3 seconds of speech)
   - `voiceover` type
   - `tone` of voice
   - `music_type` (if detectable from audio)
4. Merge all frame-level tags, deduplicate, keep highest-confidence version

**For Carousel:**
1. Tag each card separately (as images)
2. Add carousel-level tags: `card_count`, `story_arc` (if cards tell a sequential story)

#### Step 3: Tag Storage
- Insert all extracted tags into `cim_creative_tags`
- Update `cim_creative_assets.status` = `tagged`
- Update `tagging_completed_at` = now()

#### Step 4: Daily Tag Performance Aggregation (Cron — runs daily at 2 AM ET)

```sql
-- Pseudocode for the daily aggregation job
FOR each unique (tag_category, tag_name, brand, platform) combination:

  1. Find all creative assets that have this tag
  2. Join to umdm_metrics_daily for the past 7d, 14d, 30d windows
  3. Aggregate: SUM(spend), SUM(impressions), SUM(clicks), SUM(conversions), SUM(revenue)
  4. Calculate: avg_ctr, avg_cpc, avg_cpa, avg_roas, avg_conversion_rate
  5. Calculate statistical significance:
     - Minimum 1,000 impressions AND $100 spend for significance
     - Use chi-squared test for CTR differences vs. category average
  6. UPSERT into cim_tag_performance
```

#### Step 5: Fatigue Detection (Cron — runs every 12 hours)

For each active creative asset:
1. Pull daily metrics for the past 14 days from UMDM
2. Calculate 3-day rolling average for: CTR, ROAS, CPA, conversion rate
3. Compare current 3-day avg to the 3-day avg from 7 days ago
4. Score the decline:

```
Fatigue Score Algorithm:
  ctr_decline = (ctr_7d_ago - ctr_now) / ctr_7d_ago
  roas_decline = (roas_7d_ago - roas_now) / roas_7d_ago
  frequency = current_frequency

  IF frequency > 4.0 AND (ctr_decline > 0.30 OR roas_decline > 0.30):
    alert_type = 'critical', severity = 5
  ELIF frequency > 3.0 AND (ctr_decline > 0.20 OR roas_decline > 0.20):
    alert_type = 'declining', severity = 4
  ELIF frequency > 2.5 AND (ctr_decline > 0.10 OR roas_decline > 0.10):
    alert_type = 'early_warning', severity = 3
  ELIF trend shows 3+ consecutive daily declines in CTR or ROAS:
    alert_type = 'early_warning', severity = 2

  estimated_days_remaining = extrapolate decline rate to reach 50% of peak performance
```

5. Insert alert into `cim_fatigue_alerts`
6. Generate AI recommendation using GPT-4o:
   - Reference the creative's tags to suggest what to keep (performing elements) and what to change
   - Cross-reference with top-performing tags in `cim_tag_performance` to suggest replacements

### 2.7 Frontend — Dashboard Pages (React + Tailwind)

Build these as new pages within the Ad Campaign Engine app (adengine.insightprofit.live):

#### Page 1: Creative Intelligence Dashboard (`/creative-intelligence`)
- **Header:** "Creative Intelligence" with brand filter (FGS, FF, IP, FP, SS) and date range picker (7d, 14d, 30d, 90d, custom)
- **Top KPI Cards:** Total Creatives Analyzed | Avg ROAS | Top Performing Element | Creatives Needing Refresh
- **Tag Performance Heatmap:** Grid of tag_category × top 5 tag_names, colored by ROAS (green = high, red = low). Click any cell to drill into the detail view.
- **Top 10 Winning Elements Table:**

```
| Rank | Element Category | Element | Creatives | Avg ROAS | Avg CTR | Avg CPA | Spend |
|------|-----------------|---------|-----------|----------|---------|---------|-------|
| 1    | hook_type       | question| 23        | 4.2x     | 3.8%    | $12.40  | $4,200|
| 2    | face_emotion    | happy   | 31        | 3.9x     | 3.5%    | $13.10  | $6,100|
...
```

- **Bottom 10 Losing Elements Table:** Same format, sorted ascending by ROAS
- **Fatigue Alert Panel:** Red/yellow/green cards for each active alert, with "View Creative" and "Mark Acknowledged" actions

#### Page 2: Creative Deep Dive (`/creative-intelligence/:assetId`)
- **Creative Preview:** Image/video player on the left
- **Tag List:** All extracted tags on the right, grouped by category. Each tag shows its performance vs category average (arrow up/down + color).
- **Performance Timeline:** Line chart showing this creative's CTR, ROAS, CPA over time with fatigue annotations
- **Element Contribution Analysis:** Bar chart showing which tagged elements correlate with this creative's performance
- **Recommendation Card:** AI-generated suggestion for iteration (what to keep, what to change)

#### Page 3: Tag Explorer (`/creative-intelligence/tags`)
- **Search/filter by tag category and tag name**
- **For each tag:** performance metrics, trend chart, number of creatives, top 3 creatives using this tag (with thumbnails)
- **Compare mode:** Select 2 tags side-by-side to compare their performance metrics

### 2.8 API Endpoints

All endpoints live under the existing Convex backend or a new Supabase Edge Function set:

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| GET | `/api/cim/assets` | List creative assets (paginated, filterable by brand/platform/status) |
| GET | `/api/cim/assets/:id` | Get single asset with all tags |
| POST | `/api/cim/assets/ingest` | Trigger manual ingestion for a specific ad_id |
| GET | `/api/cim/tags/performance` | Tag performance leaderboard (filterable by category/brand/platform/date) |
| GET | `/api/cim/tags/:category/:name` | Deep performance data for a specific tag |
| GET | `/api/cim/fatigue/alerts` | Active fatigue alerts (filterable by severity) |
| POST | `/api/cim/fatigue/alerts/:id/acknowledge` | Mark alert as acknowledged |
| POST | `/api/cim/run-tagging` | Manually trigger tagging pipeline for pending assets |
| POST | `/api/cim/run-aggregation` | Manually trigger performance aggregation |

### 2.9 Integration Points with Existing Systems

| System | Integration | Direction |
|--------|------------|-----------|
| UMDM (`umdm_ads`, `umdm_metrics_daily`) | Pull ad creative metadata + daily performance metrics | CIM ← UMDM |
| Ad Campaign Engine Creative Factory | Tag newly generated creatives before launch (pre-tag) | CIM ← ACE |
| Ad Campaign Engine Creative Scoring | Enrich creative scoring with element-level data | CIM → ACE |
| Customer Avatar Registry | Match `customer_avatar_match` tag to 294+ avatars | CIM ← Avatars |
| Slack Alerts | Push fatigue alerts to `#adsmanagement` | CIM → Slack |

### 2.10 Cost Estimate

| Component | Cost | Notes |
|-----------|------|-------|
| GPT-4o Vision API (tagging) | ~$0.01-0.03 per image | At 200 creatives/mo = $2-6/mo |
| GPT-4o Vision (video keyframes) | ~$0.05-0.15 per video | At 50 videos/mo = $2.50-7.50/mo |
| Whisper API (audio transcription) | ~$0.006/min | At 50 videos × 30s avg = $0.15/mo |
| Supabase storage | $0 | Self-hosted, existing infra |
| **Total incremental** | **~$5-15/mo** | vs. Segwise $250-5,000+/mo |

