## 3. Feature 2: Phone Validation + SMS OTP for OfferEngine

### 3.1 Problem Statement
OfferEngine v3 captures leads through funnels but has no mechanism to verify lead quality at the point of capture. Fake phone numbers, bots, and low-quality leads waste ad spend and pollute CRM data. Heyflow offers phone network validation + SMS OTP — we need to add this to our existing funnel builder.

### 3.2 What We're Building
A lead quality validation layer within OfferEngine v3 that:
1. Validates phone numbers against carrier databases (blocks VoIP, landline, invalid numbers)
2. Optionally requires SMS OTP verification before form submission
3. Scores lead quality based on validation results + funnel behavior

### 3.3 Architecture

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    LEAD QUALITY VALIDATION LAYER                                 │
│                    OfferEngine v3 Add-On                                         │
├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                                                  │
│  ┌─────────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────────┐   │
│  │  PHONE VALIDATOR    │  │  SMS OTP ENGINE     │  │  LEAD SCORING           │   │
│  │                     │  │                     │  │                         │   │
│  │ Twilio Lookup API   │  │ Twilio Verify API   │  │ Phone validity score    │   │
│  │  • Carrier type     │  │  • Send OTP         │  │ OTP completion score    │   │
│  │  • Line type        │  │  • Verify OTP       │  │ Funnel behavior score   │   │
│  │  • Country match    │  │  • Rate limiting     │  │ Combined quality grade  │   │
│  │  • Number format    │  │  • Retry logic       │  │ (A/B/C/D/F)            │   │
│  └─────────────────────┘  └────────────────────┘  └─────────────────────────┘   │
│                                                                                  │
│  Uses: Twilio Lookup API ($0.005/lookup) + Twilio Verify API ($0.05/verification)│
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### 3.4 Database Schema (Convex — OfferEngine backend)

#### Table: `phoneValidations`

```typescript
// convex/schema.ts — add to existing schema
phoneValidations: defineTable({
  leadId: v.id("leads"),
  funnelId: v.id("funnels"),
  stepId: v.optional(v.id("funnelSteps")),
  phoneNumber: v.string(),           // E.164 format
  countryCode: v.string(),           // ISO 2-letter
  // Lookup results
  carrierName: v.optional(v.string()),
  carrierType: v.optional(v.string()),  // mobile | landline | voip | unknown
  lineType: v.optional(v.string()),
  isValid: v.boolean(),
  isMobile: v.boolean(),
  isVoip: v.boolean(),
  lookupError: v.optional(v.string()),
  // OTP verification
  otpRequested: v.boolean(),
  otpRequestedAt: v.optional(v.number()),
  otpVerified: v.boolean(),
  otpVerifiedAt: v.optional(v.number()),
  otpAttempts: v.number(),           // Max 3 attempts
  otpChannel: v.optional(v.string()), // sms | whatsapp
  // Quality scoring
  qualityScore: v.number(),          // 0-100
  qualityGrade: v.string(),          // A | B | C | D | F
  // Timestamps
  createdAt: v.number(),
})
  .index("by_lead", ["leadId"])
  .index("by_funnel", ["funnelId"])
  .index("by_phone", ["phoneNumber"])
  .index("by_grade", ["qualityGrade"])
  .index("by_created", ["createdAt"]),
```

#### Table: `phoneValidationSettings`

```typescript
phoneValidationSettings: defineTable({
  funnelId: v.id("funnels"),
  enabled: v.boolean(),
  // Validation level
  validationLevel: v.string(),       // 'basic' | 'carrier' | 'otp'
  // Rules
  blockVoip: v.boolean(),            // Block VoIP numbers (Google Voice, etc.)
  blockLandline: v.boolean(),        // Block landline numbers
  allowedCountries: v.array(v.string()), // ISO country codes (empty = all)
  blockedCountries: v.array(v.string()), // ISO country codes to block
  // OTP settings
  otpRequired: v.boolean(),
  otpChannel: v.string(),            // 'sms' | 'whatsapp' | 'both'
  otpExpirySeconds: v.number(),      // Default 300 (5 min)
  maxOtpAttempts: v.number(),        // Default 3
  // Branding
  otpMessageTemplate: v.optional(v.string()), // Custom OTP message
  brandName: v.optional(v.string()),          // Brand name in OTP message
  // Quality score thresholds
  minQualityScore: v.number(),       // Minimum score to accept lead (0-100)
  // Updated
  updatedAt: v.number(),
})
  .index("by_funnel", ["funnelId"]),
```

### 3.5 API Integration (Twilio)

#### Twilio Lookup API (Phone Validation)

```typescript
// convex/phoneValidation.ts

import { v } from "convex/values";
import { action } from "./_generated/server";

// Configuration
const TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID = process.env.TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID;
const TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN = process.env.TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN;
const TWILIO_VERIFY_SERVICE_SID = process.env.TWILIO_VERIFY_SERVICE_SID;

// Action: Validate phone number via Twilio Lookup
export const validatePhone = action({
  args: {
    phoneNumber: v.string(),
    countryCode: v.string(),
    funnelId: v.id("funnels"),
    stepId: v.optional(v.id("funnelSteps")),
  },
  handler: async (ctx, args) => {
    // 1. Format to E.164
    const e164 = formatToE164(args.phoneNumber, args.countryCode);
    
    // 2. Call Twilio Lookup API v2
    const lookupUrl = `https://lookups.twilio.com/v2/PhoneNumbers/${e164}?Fields=line_type_intelligence`;
    const response = await fetch(lookupUrl, {
      headers: {
        "Authorization": "Basic " + btoa(`${TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID}:${TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN}`),
      },
    });
    const data = await response.json();
    
    // 3. Parse results
    const lineTypeInfo = data.line_type_intelligence || {};
    const carrierType = lineTypeInfo.type || "unknown"; // mobile | landline | voip | ...
    const isMobile = carrierType === "mobile";
    const isVoip = carrierType === "voip" || carrierType === "nonFixedVoip";
    const isValid = data.valid;
    
    // 4. Return validation result
    return {
      phoneNumber: e164,
      isValid,
      isMobile,
      isVoip,
      carrierName: lineTypeInfo.carrier_name || null,
      carrierType,
      lineType: lineTypeInfo.type,
    };
  },
});

// Action: Send OTP via Twilio Verify
export const sendOtp = action({
  args: {
    phoneNumber: v.string(),
    channel: v.string(), // 'sms' or 'whatsapp'
  },
  handler: async (ctx, args) => {
    const verifyUrl = `https://verify.twilio.com/v2/Services/${TWILIO_VERIFY_SERVICE_SID}/Verifications`;
    const response = await fetch(verifyUrl, {
      method: "POST",
      headers: {
        "Authorization": "Basic " + btoa(`${TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID}:${TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN}`),
        "Content-Type": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded",
      },
      body: new URLSearchParams({
        To: args.phoneNumber,
        Channel: args.channel,
      }),
    });
    const data = await response.json();
    return {
      success: data.status === "pending",
      sid: data.sid,
    };
  },
});

// Action: Verify OTP code
export const verifyOtp = action({
  args: {
    phoneNumber: v.string(),
    code: v.string(),
  },
  handler: async (ctx, args) => {
    const checkUrl = `https://verify.twilio.com/v2/Services/${TWILIO_VERIFY_SERVICE_SID}/VerificationCheck`;
    const response = await fetch(checkUrl, {
      method: "POST",
      headers: {
        "Authorization": "Basic " + btoa(`${TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID}:${TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN}`),
        "Content-Type": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded",
      },
      body: new URLSearchParams({
        To: args.phoneNumber,
        Code: args.code,
      }),
    });
    const data = await response.json();
    return {
      verified: data.status === "approved",
      status: data.status,
    };
  },
});
```

### 3.6 Lead Quality Scoring Algorithm

```
Quality Score (0-100) = weighted sum of:

  Phone Validity (30 points max):
    Valid mobile number:        30
    Valid landline:             15
    Valid VoIP:                 5
    Invalid number:             0

  OTP Verification (40 points max):
    OTP verified on 1st attempt:  40
    OTP verified on 2nd attempt:  30
    OTP verified on 3rd attempt:  20
    OTP not attempted (not required): 25
    OTP failed all attempts:      0

  Funnel Behavior (30 points max):
    Time on funnel > 60s:         10
    Completed 2+ steps:           10
    Didn't rush (not bot-speed):  10
    Rush-submitted (<5s):         0

  Quality Grade:
    A: 80-100  (high quality — verified, engaged)
    B: 60-79   (good quality — mostly verified)
    C: 40-59   (medium quality — some concerns)
    D: 20-39   (low quality — likely fake/bot)
    F: 0-19    (reject — block submission)
```

### 3.7 Frontend — UI Components

#### Component 1: Phone Input with Validation (`PhoneValidationInput.tsx`)
- Country code dropdown (flag + code) — default based on browser locale
- Phone number input with real-time formatting
- On blur or after 10 digits: trigger `validatePhone` API call
- Show inline status:
  - ✅ Green checkmark: "Mobile number verified"
  - ⚠️ Yellow warning: "VoIP number detected" (if `blockVoip` is false)
  - ❌ Red error: "Invalid number" or "VoIP numbers not accepted"
- Loading spinner during validation

#### Component 2: OTP Verification Modal (`OtpVerificationModal.tsx`)
- Appears after phone validation passes (if OTP required)
- 6-digit code input (individual box per digit, auto-advance)
- "Resend code" link with 60-second countdown
- 3 attempt limit, then "Contact support" message
- Auto-submit when all 6 digits entered
- Success: green animation → close modal → continue funnel
- Failure: shake animation → "Incorrect code, X attempts remaining"

#### Component 3: Funnel Builder Settings (`PhoneValidationSettings.tsx`)
- New section in the funnel builder settings panel
- Toggle: "Enable Phone Validation"
- Radio: Validation Level (Basic / Carrier Check / Full OTP)
- Toggles: Block VoIP, Block Landlines
- Country restrictions: Multi-select for allowed/blocked countries
- OTP channel: SMS / WhatsApp / Both
- Quality score threshold slider (0-100)
- Preview: shows what the user will see at each validation level

#### Component 4: Lead Quality Dashboard Widget
- Add to existing OfferEngine dashboard
- Donut chart: Lead quality distribution (A/B/C/D/F grades)
- Table: Recent leads with quality score, validation status, OTP status
- Stat cards: "Average Lead Quality Score", "Leads Blocked", "OTP Verification Rate"

