## 4. Feature 3: Competitor Ad Monitoring System

### 4.1 Problem Statement
We have no automated system to track competitor ad creatives across platforms. Our Ad Campaign Engine's Data Intelligence module has a "Competitor Intel" placeholder but it only does basic web scraping. Segwise.ai offers competitor ad library tracking — we need an automated system that monitors competitors and feeds insights into our creative strategy.

### 4.2 What We're Building
A multi-platform competitor ad monitoring system that:
1. Tracks specified competitors' active ads across Meta Ad Library and TikTok Creative Center
2. Auto-tags competitor creatives using the same CIM tag taxonomy (Feature 1)
3. Surfaces trending creative patterns, new campaign launches, and competitive insights
4. Feeds insights directly into our Creative Factory for data-informed creative generation

### 4.3 Architecture

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    COMPETITOR AD MONITORING SYSTEM (CAMS)                         │
├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                                                  │
│  ┌──────────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────────┐  │
│  │  DATA COLLECTORS     │  │  AI ANALYZER         │  │  INSIGHT DASHBOARD     │  │
│  │                      │  │                      │  │                        │  │
│  │  Meta Ad Library API │  │  GPT-4o Vision       │  │  Trending elements     │  │
│  │  TikTok Creative Ctr │  │  Same tag taxonomy   │  │  New campaign alerts   │  │
│  │  Google Ads          │  │  as CIM (Feature 1)  │  │  Gap analysis          │  │
│  │  Transparency Ctr    │  │  Competitor vs. ours  │  │  Creative brief gen    │  │
│  │  (Manual: LinkedIn,  │  │  comparison engine   │  │  Opportunity alerts    │  │
│  │   Pinterest, other)  │  │                      │  │                        │  │
│  └──────────┬───────────┘  └──────────┬───────────┘  └────────────┬───────────┘  │
│             └──────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────┘               │
│                                        ▼                                          │
│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │
│  │                     SUPABASE — cams_* tables                                │ │
│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### 4.4 Database Schema (Supabase)

#### Table: `cams_competitors`

```sql
CREATE TABLE cams_competitors (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  brand TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (brand IN ('fgs','ff','ip','fp','ss')),
  competitor_name TEXT NOT NULL,
  competitor_url TEXT,
  -- Platform identifiers
  meta_page_id TEXT,               -- Facebook Page ID for Ad Library
  meta_page_name TEXT,             -- Facebook Page name
  tiktok_advertiser_id TEXT,       -- TikTok advertiser ID
  google_advertiser_id TEXT,       -- Google Ads Transparency Center ID
  -- Tracking config
  is_active BOOLEAN DEFAULT true,
  check_frequency_hours INTEGER DEFAULT 24,
  last_checked_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
  -- Metadata
  industry TEXT,
  estimated_monthly_spend TEXT,    -- rough bracket: <10K, 10-50K, 50-250K, 250K+
  notes TEXT,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),
  updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
);
```

#### Table: `cams_competitor_ads`

```sql
CREATE TABLE cams_competitor_ads (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  competitor_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES cams_competitors(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  platform TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (platform IN ('meta','tiktok','google','linkedin','pinterest')),
  platform_ad_id TEXT,              -- Platform-specific ad ID
  ad_url TEXT,                      -- Direct link to the ad (Ad Library URL)
  creative_type TEXT CHECK (creative_type IN ('image','video','carousel','collection','text')),
  creative_url TEXT,                -- URL to the creative asset
  thumbnail_url TEXT,
  -- Ad metadata (from library)
  ad_copy_primary TEXT,             -- Primary text
  ad_copy_headline TEXT,            -- Headline
  ad_copy_description TEXT,         -- Description
  ad_copy_cta TEXT,                 -- CTA button text
  landing_page_url TEXT,
  -- Activity tracking
  first_seen_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),
  last_seen_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),
  is_active BOOLEAN DEFAULT true,
  estimated_days_running INTEGER,
  -- Tagging (same taxonomy as CIM)
  tagging_status TEXT DEFAULT 'pending',
  tags JSONB DEFAULT '[]',          -- Array of {category, name, value, confidence}
  -- Analysis
  ai_analysis TEXT,                 -- GPT-4o analysis summary
  competitive_angle TEXT,           -- What angle they're taking
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
);

CREATE INDEX idx_cams_ads_competitor ON cams_competitor_ads(competitor_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_cams_ads_platform ON cams_competitor_ads(platform);
CREATE INDEX idx_cams_ads_active ON cams_competitor_ads(is_active);
CREATE INDEX idx_cams_ads_first_seen ON cams_competitor_ads(first_seen_at DESC);
```

#### Table: `cams_trend_reports`

```sql
CREATE TABLE cams_trend_reports (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  brand TEXT NOT NULL,
  report_type TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (report_type IN ('weekly','monthly','alert')),
  period_start DATE NOT NULL,
  period_end DATE NOT NULL,
  -- Report content
  summary TEXT NOT NULL,
  trending_elements JSONB,          -- [{tag_category, tag_name, frequency, trend_direction}]
  new_campaigns_detected INTEGER,
  competitors_analyzed INTEGER,
  key_insights JSONB,               -- [{insight, source_competitor, actionability}]
  creative_brief_suggestions JSONB, -- [{concept, rationale, inspired_by}]
  -- Status
  delivered_via TEXT,                -- 'slack' | 'dashboard' | 'both'
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
);
```

### 4.5 Data Collection Pipeline (SOP)

#### Source 1: Meta Ad Library API

```
Endpoint: https://graph.facebook.com/v21.0/ads_archive
Method: GET
Auth: Meta Marketing API access token (long-lived page token)

Parameters:
  ad_reached_countries: ['US']
  search_page_ids: [competitor's Facebook Page ID]
  ad_active_status: 'ACTIVE'  (or 'ALL' for history)
  fields: ad_creative_bodies,ad_creative_link_captions,ad_creative_link_descriptions,
          ad_creative_link_titles,ad_delivery_start_time,ad_delivery_stop_time,
          estimated_audience_size,impressions,page_id,page_name,
          publisher_platforms,ad_snapshot_url
  limit: 100

Rate Limits: 200 calls/hour per access token
```

**Collection Flow:**
1. For each active competitor with a `meta_page_id`:
   - Call Meta Ad Library API with their page ID
   - For each returned ad:
     a. Check if `platform_ad_id` already exists in `cams_competitor_ads`
     b. If new: insert with `first_seen_at` = now, download creative from `ad_snapshot_url`
     c. If exists: update `last_seen_at` = now, `is_active` = true
   - For existing ads NOT in the API response: mark `is_active` = false
2. Trigger AI tagging for all new/updated ads (same pipeline as CIM Feature 1)
3. Update `cams_competitors.last_checked_at`

#### Source 2: TikTok Creative Center (Web Scraping)

TikTok does not have a public API for their Creative Center. Use headless browser scraping:

```
Target URL: https://ads.tiktok.com/business/creativecenter/inspiration/topads/pc/en
Method: Headless browser (Puppeteer/Playwright)

Steps:
1. Navigate to TikTok Creative Center Top Ads
2. Filter by: country, industry/vertical, ad format, time period
3. Scrape ad cards: video thumbnail, ad copy, engagement metrics, advertiser name
4. For each ad matching our tracked competitor names:
   - Download video thumbnail/preview
   - Extract visible copy text
   - Insert into cams_competitor_ads
5. Rate limit: 1 request per 5 seconds, rotate user agents
```

**Note:** TikTok Creative Center scraping is less reliable than Meta Ad Library API. Implement graceful failure handling with retry logic.

#### Source 3: Google Ads Transparency Center (Web Scraping)

```
Target URL: https://adstransparency.google.com/advertiser/{advertiser_id}
Method: Headless browser (Puppeteer/Playwright)

Steps:
1. Navigate to advertiser's transparency page
2. Extract: ad creatives (images/text), date ranges, platforms (Search/Display/YouTube)
3. For each ad: download creative, extract copy text
4. Insert into cams_competitor_ads
```

### 4.6 Analysis Pipeline (Cron — runs weekly on Monday 6 AM ET)

#### Step 1: Tag All Untagged Competitor Ads
- Query `cams_competitor_ads WHERE tagging_status = 'pending'`
- Run through same GPT-4o Vision tagging pipeline as CIM (Feature 1)
- Store tags in the `tags` JSONB column

#### Step 2: Trend Detection

```
For each brand:
  1. Pull all competitor ads from the past 7 days
  2. Aggregate tag frequencies: 
     - Count occurrences of each (tag_category, tag_name) 
  3. Compare to previous 7-day period:
     - Rising: >30% increase in frequency
     - Falling: >30% decrease in frequency
     - New: tag not seen in previous period
  4. Generate trending_elements array
```

#### Step 3: Gap Analysis (Our Creatives vs. Competitors)

```
For each brand:
  1. Pull our creative tags from cim_creative_tags (Feature 1)
  2. Pull competitor tags from cams_competitor_ads
  3. Identify:
     a. Tags competitors use that we DON'T → Opportunities
     b. Tags we use that competitors DON'T → Our differentiators
     c. Tags both use → Competitive parity (review who does it better)
  4. Rank opportunities by: competitor performance × our gap size
```

#### Step 4: AI Report Generation

Send the trend data + gap analysis to GPT-4o with this prompt:

```
You are a competitive intelligence analyst for an ecommerce ad agency managing 5 brands.

Given the following competitor ad data from the past week:
- [trending elements]
- [gap analysis: opportunities vs. differentiators]
- [new campaigns detected]

Generate:
1. Executive summary (3-4 sentences)
2. Top 3 actionable insights (with specific recommendations)
3. 2 creative brief suggestions inspired by competitor successes
4. Risk alerts (any competitor moves that threaten our position)

Format as structured JSON matching the cams_trend_reports schema.
```

#### Step 5: Store + Deliver
- Insert into `cams_trend_reports`
- Post summary to Slack `#adsmanagement` channel
- Update dashboard

### 4.7 Frontend — Dashboard Pages

#### Page 1: Competitor Monitor (`/competitor-monitor`)
- **Competitor Cards:** Grid showing each tracked competitor with: name, platforms monitored, active ad count, last checked, overall activity trend (↑/↓/→)
- **"Add Competitor" Button:** Modal to enter competitor name, website, platform page IDs
- **Timeline View:** Chronological feed of new competitor ads detected, sorted by recency

#### Page 2: Competitor Detail (`/competitor-monitor/:competitorId`)
- **Ad Gallery:** Grid of all ads (image thumbnails / video previews), filterable by platform, active/inactive, date range
- **Tag Cloud:** Visual cloud of most-used creative elements by this competitor
- **Copy Patterns:** Most common headline formulas, CTAs, hook types
- **Activity Timeline:** When they launch, pause, and refresh creatives
- **Click any ad** → Expand to see full creative, all tags, copy text, landing page URL, estimated run duration

#### Page 3: Trend Report (`/competitor-monitor/trends`)
- **Latest Report Card:** Rendered version of `cams_trend_reports`
- **Trending Elements Chart:** Bar chart showing rising/falling tag trends across all competitors
- **Gap Analysis Table:**

```
| Element           | Competitors Using | We Use? | Opportunity Score | Action     |
|-------------------|-------------------|---------|-------------------|------------|
| ugc_testimonial   | 4/5 competitors   | No      | HIGH              | Test this  |
| countdown_timer   | 3/5 competitors   | No      | MEDIUM            | Consider   |
| question_hook     | 5/5 competitors   | Yes     | PARITY            | Improve    |
```

- **Creative Brief Suggestions:** Rendered cards from AI-generated brief suggestions with "Generate Creative" button (links to Creative Factory)

