## Appendix A: Customer Avatar Integration Reference

The Creative Intelligence Module should reference our Customer Avatar Registry (294+ avatars across 5 brands) when tagging the `customer_avatar_match` element. The registry is stored at:

```
skills/customer_avatars/registry/master_avatar_registry.json
```

Structure per avatar:
```json
{
  "avatar_id": "fgs_gift_giver_01",
  "brand": "fgs",
  "name": "The Thoughtful Gift-Giver",
  "demographics": { "age_range": "35-54", "gender": "female", ... },
  "psychographics": { "mbti": "ENFJ", "enneagram": "2w3", ... },
  "pain_points": ["Finding unique gifts", "Personalization options", ...],
  "buying_triggers": ["Holidays", "Birthdays", "Milestones", ...]
}
```

When the AI tagger identifies demographic/psychographic signals in a creative (e.g., female 35-54, lifestyle context = home, emotion = happy), it should match against the avatar registry and tag the closest avatar ID.

---

## Appendix B: Existing UMDM Tables Referenced

These existing Supabase tables provide the performance data for CIM:

| Table | Key Fields | Used For |
|-------|-----------|----------|
| `umdm_ads` | ad_id, campaign_id, ad_set_id, brand, channel, creative_url, status | Link CIM assets to ad platform data |
| `umdm_metrics_daily` | ad_id, date, spend, impressions, clicks, conversions, revenue | Daily performance metrics per ad |
| `umdm_campaigns` | campaign_id, brand, channel, objective, budget | Campaign-level context |
| `umdm_ad_sets` | ad_set_id, campaign_id, targeting, audience | Audience context for avatar matching |

---

## Appendix C: Naming Convention for All New Tables

All new tables follow existing InsightProfit conventions:
- Feature 1 (Creative Intelligence Module): prefix `cim_`
- Feature 3 (Competitor Ad Monitoring): prefix `cams_`
- Feature 2 (Phone Validation): integrated into OfferEngine's existing Convex schema (no prefix, follows Convex naming)

